  "prompt": "When one should eat after workout?",
  "response": "Eating after a workout is important for recovery. Generally, it is recommended to eat within 30 minutes to 2 hours after completing your workout. This time frame can help maximize the benefits of your exercise session, such as muscle recovery and replenishment of glycogen stores.\n\nYour post-workout meal should ideally include a balance of proteins and carbohydrates. Proteins help repair and build muscle tissue, while carbohydrates replenish glycogen stores. Adding a small amount of healthy fats can also be beneficial. Some examples of good post-workout snacks or meals include:\n\n1. A protein shake with banana or berries.\n2. Greek yogurt with honey and granola.\n3. A sandwich with lean meat, whole grain bread, and avocado.\n4. Rice with chicken and vegetables.\n5. Cottage cheese with fruits.\n\nRemember, staying hydrated is equally important, so drinking water or a sports drink can help rehydrate and replenish electrolytes lost during exercise.",
